{[show S]
South holds two long suits and must decide which one to name first. With two five-card suits, rank decides.
[BID 1H]
With two suits of equal length, @S @v(open|opens) the higher-ranking one, so the hearts come first and @v(plan|plans) to show the diamonds later. That keeps the bidding cheap and lets partner picture the shape.
[show N]
North has a modest hand but a fit and a few useful cards opposite an opening bid.
[BID 2H]
